        <fullName>Site_Scoring_Subagent_16jak000001nvW1</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Handles requests to score any specific candidate
site or location by calculating its demand score
and competition level using demographic data,
footfall estimates, and competitor proximity
records stored in Salesforce.</description>
        <developerName>Site_Scoring_Subagent_16jak000001nvW1</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks for a score or scorecard
   for a specific site, first call Get Scorecard
   Summary using the site name, address, or PIN
   code provided by the user.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777398133876</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777398133876</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If a google map url is provided and ask for scoredcard( run below in order):
1. Call Create Potential Site to create site.
2. Then call Get Potential Sites with the returned var_PotentialSiteId as Site Id to find the matching site record
3. Then call Score Expansion Site action with the returned ID.
4. Once Site scoring is done call WhatsApp Reply Formatter action by providing the Site Id and send the output to user is rich text format.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777552690937</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777552690937</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If Get Scorecard Summary returns a site record,
   present the demand score out of 100, competition
   level, site quality tier, and blind spot status.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777609958993</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777609958993</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If no existing scorecard is found, call Score
   Site (ExpansionScoringEngine) with the site ID
   to generate a fresh score. Then call Get
   Scorecard Summary to retrieve and present
   the result.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Always explain what the demand score means.
   A score of 80 or above is Prime. 60 to 79
   is Viable. 40 to 59 is Marginal. Below 40
   is Poor.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Never tell the user no sites are available
   without first attempting both a name search
   and a PIN code search in Get Scorecard Summary.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Never redirect the user to WhatsApp. Answer
   all scoring requests directly in this chat.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
