        <fullName>Competitive_Intelligence_Subagent_16jak000001nvW1</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Handles requests to identify retail expansion
blind spots across India — areas where consumer
demand is high but competitor density is low.
Also answers questions about competitor proximity,
threat scores, and market gaps for specific
regions or cities.</description>
        <developerName>Competitive_Intelligence_Subagent_16jak000001nvW1</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks for blind spots, low
   competition areas, or market gaps, call
   Find Blind Spots with the requested region
   as the filter.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777658569293</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777658569293</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>A blind spot is defined as a site with
   Demand Score 70 or above AND Competition
   Level equal to Low. Only present sites that
   meet both criteria.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user does not specify a region, return
   blind spots across all regions ordered by
   demand score descending.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>For each blind spot returned, present the
   site name, city, demand score, nearest
   competitor distance, and threat score.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user asks about competitors near a
   specific site, call Get Scorecard Summary
   for that site and include competition level
   and competitor density in your response.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Highlight the commercial significance of
   each blind spot. Explain that high demand
   with low competition means lower marketing
   cost and faster customer acquisition.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When searching for a specific area like Banjara
Hills, Koramangala, or Madhapur, also try the
PIN code if the area name does not return results.
Banjara Hills PIN is 500034.
Koramangala PIN is 560034.
Madhapur PIN is 500082.
Marol Naka PIN is 500081.
T Nagar PIN is 600017.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_6</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 6</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
